summary:
I want Moomin, Little My, and Snufkin to all be generic, coming-of-age hero story protagonists.
Little My is the chaotic one who...
body:
I want Moomin, Little My, and Snufkin to all be generic, coming-of-age hero story protagonists.

Little My is the chaotic one who also serves to make Moomin frustrated until they can finally reconcile at a really emotional point.

Snufkin tries to pretend he’s the voice of reason but in all honesty he just says very little because his thoughts are dumb as all fuck.

Moomin knows he’s the center of attention but he actually has less specialties and skills than both Little My and Snufkin so he tries to constantly prove himself with his platform.

summary: I just had some very disturbing thoughts
title: I just had some very disturbing thoughts
body:
What if the new Moominvalley cartoon does end up coming to America and they end up hiring different voice actors, like what happened with Bob the Builder?

Or what if they decide to put interstitials or a framing device around the episodes, like they did with Thomas the Tank Engine and Noddy?
